      "content": "Minimum wage hikes in rural areas often force small businesses to either absorb the cost through reduced profit margins or pass the burden onto customers via higher prices. Since rural coffee shops rely heavily on thin margins and volume, even a small mandatory raise can be financially devastating without a corresponding increase in sales. You should absolutely factor these potential costs into your business plan, as they significantly impact your long-term viability in a low-cost environment.",
